  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to determine if a mobile sensing platform can passively and
      objectively detect the presence of clinically significant mood disorder symptomatology and
      symptom progression over time. Meeting this goal will allow for improved risk categorization,
      prediction of relapse, and measurement of disease progression in a lifetime prevalence
      population.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
